## 16. Artificial Intelligence Restrictions

Notwithstanding any other provision of this License, no rights are
granted to use the Software or any portion thereof for the purpose of
developing, training, fine-tuning, evaluating, benchmarking, or
improving any machine learning or artificial intelligence system without
the prior written permission of the Licensor.

This prohibition includes, but is not limited to: - Training or
fine-tuning large language models (LLMs). - Training or improving code
generation models. - Creating datasets derived from the Software. -
Generating embeddings or vector databases from the Software for AI model
development or retrieval. - Using the Software as benchmark, evaluation,
or test data for AI systems. - Automated scraping, indexing, or
extraction of the Software for AI training purposes.

This restriction applies whether the Software is used in whole or in
part, directly or indirectly.

Any person or entity that violates this Section immediately loses all
rights granted under this License.

Nothing in this Section prohibits AI-assisted development tools that
operate solely for the benefit of the Licensee during software
development and do not use the Software to train or improve an AI model.